race.comment: Lots of these find it hard to win. APPPLEBY (3) has won just one of 21 but has racked up 10 minors - the last five on end and all three this time in. Looks well placed here and expected to go close again. Same for SNAPPY PIERRO (5). Was a winner six back and has run a string of good races but finds it hard to return to winning form. Was good at Sandown last time with an on-speed placing and will take beating again with a repeat. JUSTDOIT (1) was good fresh then disappointing in tougher last time at Cranbourne. Freshened and worth another try. LA BELLE GRANDE (6) was thereabouts fresh but strips fitter and rates highly on best form. Expecting big improvement. TAKE THE PRIZE (2) has been mixing form but has the ability and can run well at odds.
